Blue Martini...I'm giving you 3 stars.
This isn't based on any particular visit, but my overall experience with the establishment after visiting the place for the past 1-1/2 to 2 years.
Happy Hour 7 days a week from 4:00pm to 8:00pm makes it one of the most accessible happy hours in town.
No weekdays only or happy hours ending when you get off work; if happy hour didn't have such a generous time slot I probably would have stopped coming here a while ago.
What does happy hour get you?
Why, 1/2 off all martini's and food on the menu!
Servers have also told me that the 1/2 off price applies to mixed drinks with 1 spirit, though I haven't confirmed this.
So part of me wants to give this place 4 stars, but those 4 stars are only based on the happy hour.
Drinks are regularly priced at $12-$16, though you do get the shaker with the rest of your drink.
Come during happy hour and you're almost getting two drinks for $6-$8, very worth it.
Food is also in the same price range, and the food is good, but not good enough for me to purchase at full price.
This place doesn't get 5 stars because nothing has been spectacular to me, but the value of what you get versus what you pay (during happy hour) is good.
In the end though, Blue Martini ends up with 3 stars, being average to me.
The biggest factor is service; and I'm not just talking about slow service.
There have been several occasions where my order has taken over 20 minutes to arrive, was taken by another waitress to another customer, or was just not put in in the first place.
I guess I can understand waiting a bit for a flatbread if there are 50 people ordering it at the same time, but I can't understand how another customer can end up with my order, or hearing the waitress tell me that she forgot to put the order in.
Service can be seriously lacking when things are busy.
Though if you arrive right at 4:00pm (both the start of happy hour and their opening), you should have no problem getting a couple drinks, some food, and being on your merry way before the place gets packed.
So those three stars up there...thats based on happy hour.
$25 can get you an appetizer and almost four drinks (two drinks + their respective shakers), so thats a hard offer to pass up.
Go during prime time where your order gets lost, or if you go during non-happy hour?
Then this place is a two star establishment with expensive prices and bad service.

