I work in the industry so I have a hospitality blue card that gets me 50% off food and drinks, that helps out a lot.
I also always sit out on the patio so I don't really deal with the dance floor scene.
I understand that given those facts, I am not really reviewing this place as a whole, but for a place that I know has a wide selection of strong martinis and outdoor seating I'm happy.
If you're looking for a good crowd to get your dance on, you might also enjoy it here.
Would I go here if I didn't get a discount?
No.
Is it a good alternative to the strip or a small local bar for a couple of quick drinks?
Yes.

