Happy Hour martinis, appetizers, and great service?
If these three appeal to you, the Blue Martini is the place to be from 4-8pm.
With half off beverages and up to 50% of off food, you will be enjoying an evening in a great atmosphere with lively waiters.
The setting of the restaurant/bar is also a plus since the outside bar has a cabana feel and in the inside has a club feel.
(if you get the blue martini which comes with a small glowstick, you will be ready to light up the dance floor!).
As far as the food goes, I suggest the seared ahi tuna platter.
This comes with a delicious and refreshing seaweed salad paired with some freshly grated ginger and wasabi.
The shrimp and crab dish is also a must order.
It comes with toasted crostini bread points.

Every local by now I'm sure would agree that Blue is the ultimate backup, "if all else fails" destination.
I give it three starts because there isn't much happening here anymore other than great outdoor seating and decent drink prices (compared to other places in town.
) Music is A-okay, crowd is A-okay, atmosphere is upbeat no matter when you go.
If you're in the gaming industry and have a Blue Martini card you get 50% off drinks.
Can't complain, right?
Blue Martini, spice it up a bit!

