Blue Martini is sort of the Cheesecake Factory of bars.
Don't expect anything exceptionally good.
There is a vibrant bar scene and a nice patio.
The bartenders are sloppy and inconsistent.
Also, don't plan on getting a craft cocktail or any fresh ingredients.
The food is edible.
Prices are great if you take advantage of happy hour or industry discounts.
It's a fun environment but the bottomline is there are hundreds of places with better food and drinks around town.

