Blue Martini is an okay option.
I am not always the biggest fan of this place, I have only been at the choice of a group of friends or for work social events.
They do have a good selection of cocktails.
The food is decent, nothing that I can recommend as a must try.
The prices are pretty much comparable to being on the strip.
They have live music occasionally and some dancing, the music varies between bands and DJs, depending on the night/time.
Happy Hour is a good option here (drinks are 50% off), and some of the food is discounted.
It can get really crowded, and all seating is on a first come, first serve basis.

